The Quickloc8 app is now putting control of minibus taxi drivers in the hands of taxi bosses. CAPE TOWN - Many road users are frustrated by minibus taxis, with drivers often appearing to be a law unto themselves. But what if technology could change this? A new cellphone app is doing just that. READ:Â 'Stop overloading vehicles' - Mbalula on taxi tragedy The Quickloc8 app allows owners to keep tabs on their vehicles, and if necessary, bring a reckless driver to a stop with the push of a button via a tiny device installed in the taxi. It's already been named 2018's most innovative business in the Western Cape and it's penetrated 35 percent of the local taxi industry.